  "texts": [
    "This has led to the exploration of machine learning and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques, which offer the ability to learn and adapt to new spam trends over time [5], [6].The SpamAssassin public mail corpus, developed by the Apache Software Foundation, represents a pivotal resource in this domain, and it is a publicly available dataset consisting of thousands of hand-classified email messages, marked as spam or legitimate [7], [8].",
    "This corpus has been widely utilized by researchers and practitioners alike to train and evaluate spam detection models.",
    "The value of the SpamAssassin corpus lies in its diversity and representativeness, encompassing a wide range of spam tactics and themes, and it also includes a rich set of features extracted from the email headers and bodies, providing a comprehensive basis for testing the effectiveness of various spam detection algorithms [7], [9].In recent developments, AI models such as ChatGPT-4 by OpenAI and Google Gemini have demonstrated remarkable capabilities in natural language understanding and generation, opening new avenues for spam detection [10], [11].",
    "ChatGPT-4, an iteration of the Generative Pre-trained Transformer models, has been noted for its advanced text analysis and comprehension capabilities.",
    "On the other hand, Google Gemini, representing Google's advancements in AI, offers robust tools for text classification and analysis, leveraging Google's extensive data and computational resources."
  ],
