    "The value of the SpamAssassin corpus lies in its diversity and representativeness, encompassing a wide range of spam tactics and themes, and it also includes a rich set of features extracted from the email headers and bodies, providing a comprehensive basis for testing the effectiveness of various spam detection algorithms [7], [9].In recent developments, AI models such as ChatGPT-4 by OpenAI and Google Gemini have demonstrated remarkable capabilities in natural language understanding and generation, opening new avenues for spam detection [10], [11]."
